        <section name="Use Arcanum">
            <p>
                Notice that, all the jars files can be found under the <code>jars</code> folder.
            </p>

            <a name="requirements"/>
            <subsection name="System Requirements">
                <table>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr class="b">
                            <td align="left">
                                <b>JDK</b>
                            </td>
                            <td align="left">1.6 or above
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </subsection>

            <a name="usage"/>
            <subsection name="Arcanum Usage">
                <p>
                    To use Arcanum, following jars must be included in the classpath:
                    <ol type="1">
                        <li>
                            <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-common.jar</code></span>: Common classes shared
                            among the modules.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-albegra.jar</code></span>: Algebra module.
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    In addition, there are the following modules:
                    <ol type="1">
                        <li>
                            <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-pairing.jar</code></span>: Bilinear maps.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-mm.jar</code></span>:
                            <a href="docs/pairing.html">Multilinear Maps</a>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-lattice.jar</code></span>:
                            <a href="docs/pairing.html">Lattice-Based Cryptography tools</a>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="PBC Wrapper Usage">
                <p>
                    To use the PBC Wrapper, a shared C library must be compiled
                    and installed properly as shown
                    <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/manual/ch08s03.html">here</a>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Then, to use the wrapper, include the following jars:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <span class="em"><code>arcanum_1.0.0-pbc.jar</code></span>
                        and
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="em"><code>jna-3.1.0.jar</code></span>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Cryptosystems Usage">
                <p>
                    To use the
                    <a href="schemes/schemes.html">cryptosystems</a>
                    provided by Arcanum
                    include the following jars:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <span class="em"><code>arcanum-crypto-1.0.0.jar</code></span>
                        and
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="em"><code>bcprov-jdk16-1.46</code></span>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>
